  "description": [
    "RELIGIOUS LEADERS PLEDGE AID TO OTHERS BUCK HILL FALLS Pa ANP Meeting at Buck Hill Falls in the Pacona mountains 125 religious from numerous denomi nations held a three day Con sultation on the Churches Strat egy in Relation to the Peoples of Underdeveloped Areas Among the delegates attending were Mrs Abbie Clement Jack son Louisville Ky executive secretary Womens Home and Foreign Missions society and Dr James W Eichelberger director of religious education both of the American Methodist Episcopal Zion church This meeting was held under the auspices of the National Council of Churches of Christ with offices in New York Mrs Jackson is vice president of this organization The meeting included a num ber of addresses a series of dis cussions and a program of tech nical assistance Several experts in the field of foreign missionary work and work with undedevel oped areas spoke and acted as consultants during this meeting State Senate Kills Illinois FEPC Law SPRINGFIELD 111 ANP The state senate of the Illinois General assembly last week kill ed a proposed fair employment practices law for the state by a vote of 29 to 22 A senate committee originally voted 9 to 3 to recommend"
